{"id":4064,"date":"2013-05-25T07:00:05","date_gmt":"2013-05-25T13:00:05","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/?p=4064"},"modified":"2019-11-25T17:38:46","modified_gmt":"2019-11-26T00:38:46","slug":"succulent-terrarium-tutorial-plus-helpful-tips","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/succulent-terrarium-tutorial-plus-helpful-tips\/","title":{"rendered":"How to Make a Succulent Terrarium"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><div class=\"fusion-fullwidth fullwidth-box fusion-builder-row-1 nonhundred-percent-fullwidth non-hundred-percent-height-scrolling\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0);background-position: center center;background-repeat: no-repeat;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;margin-bottom: 0px;margin-top: 0px;border-width: 0px 0px 0px 0px;border-color:#eae9e9;border-style:solid;\" ><div class=\"fusion-builder-row fusion-row\"><div class=\"fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion-builder-column-0 fusion_builder_column_1_1 1_1 fusion-one-full fusion-column-first fusion-column-last\" style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;\"><div class=\"fusion-column-wrapper fusion-flex-column-wrapper-legacy\" style=\"background-position:left top;background-repeat:no-repeat;-webkit-background-size:cover;-moz-background-size:cover;-o-background-size:cover;background-size:cover;padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\"><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-1\"><p><em>Terrariums are all the rage these days, especially succulent terrariums. Learn how to make your own with this step-by-step photo tutorial. Plus learn some dos and don'ts for using succulents in terrariums!<\/em><\/p>\n<p>A couple weeks ago when I got together with my sister-in-laws we had a \u201cfavorite things\u201d birthday party. You may remember how I left their succulent gifts outside and they got <a title=\"Extremely Sunburned Succulent Plants\" href=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/extremely-sunburned-succulent-plants\/\" rel=\"noopener\">severely sunburned<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>The idea is every gives each person a gift that costs no more than $5 and is one of your favorite things. One of the gifts we got from my sister-in-law was this cute <a href=\"https:\/\/www.amazon.com\/gp\/product\/B00BUMNEBO\/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=390957&creativeASIN=B00BUMNEBO&linkCode=as2&tag=cassituttlpho-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">glass terrarium<\/a>. I knew immediately what I wanted to do with it!<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-6254 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Learn-how-to-make-a-succulent-terrarium-and-how-to-keep-it-alive.jpg\" alt=\"Learn how to make a succulent terrarium and how to keep it alive!\" width=\"735\" height=\"1102\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Learn-how-to-make-a-succulent-terrarium-and-how-to-keep-it-alive-500x750.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Learn-how-to-make-a-succulent-terrarium-and-how-to-keep-it-alive-700x1050.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Learn-how-to-make-a-succulent-terrarium-and-how-to-keep-it-alive.jpg 735w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Last year I helped one of my sister-in-laws <a href=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/succulent-terrarium-in-an-apothecary-jar\/\" rel=\"noopener\">make a terrarium<\/a>\u00a0but it didn't last very long. For this one I wanted to make sure I planted and watered it in a way that would allow it to have a long life.<\/p>\n<h3>Start with the Right Glass Container<\/h3>\n<p>The problem with the first terrarium is that the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.amazon.com\/gp\/product\/B00JAQ893A\/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=390957&creativeASIN=B00JAQ893A&linkCode=as2&tag=cassituttlpho-20&linkId=TS4P3HMAXDS75UBT\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">apothecary jar<\/a> was so deep that water couldn't evaporate so it ended up getting moldy inside and just didn't look very pretty.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.amazon.com\/gp\/product\/B00BUMNEBO?tag=succandsunblog-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener sponsored\">This terrarium<\/a> though has a lot of things about it that will allow the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=terrarium_succulents&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Fshop%2FRanchoGarciaNursery%3Fref%3Dsearch_shop_redirect\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">succulents<\/a> to have a nice long life. The first is that it isn't very deep. Also, in addition to the main hole in front it has some smaller holes in the top that allow for airflow.<\/p>\n<p>I believe this will be crucial as succulents need to be able to dry out between watering.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-4069\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Succulent-Terrarium-Supplies-www.succulentsandsunshine.com_-500x333.jpg\" alt=\"Succulent Terrarium Supplies www.succulentsandsunshine.com\" width=\"500\" height=\"333\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Succulent-Terrarium-Supplies-www.succulentsandsunshine.com_-500x333.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Succulent-Terrarium-Supplies-www.succulentsandsunshine.com_-700x466.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Succulent-Terrarium-Supplies-www.succulentsandsunshine.com_.jpg 1000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/p>\n<h3>Tutorial<\/h3>\n<p>Here's what you'll need to make your own:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.amazon.com\/gp\/product\/B00BUMNEBO?tag=succandsunblog-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener sponsored\">Glass terrarium<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.bonsaijack.com\/Succulent_Soil_sas.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Succulent soil<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=terrarium_succulents&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Fshop%2FRanchoGarciaNursery%3Fref%3Dsearch_shop_redirect\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Succulents<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>I started by putting a little bit of soil in first. The soil I use is equal parts <a href=\"https:\/\/www.bonsaijack.com\/turface_mvp_for_bonsai_soilsas.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Turface<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.bonsaijack.com\/Pine_Bark_Fines_Standard_Sizesas.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">small pine bark shreds<\/a>, and <a href=\"https:\/\/www.bonsaijack.com\/succulent_crushed_granite_soil_ingredientsas.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">crushed rock<\/a> (Here's\u00a0<a title=\"Well draining soil for succulent container gardens\" href=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/well-draining-soil-for-succulent-container-gardens\/\" rel=\"noopener\">more about the soil<\/a>). This soil drains really well so I thought it would also work well in the terrarium to prevent too much water from building up.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-4072\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Succulent-Terrarium-Tutorial-Step-1-www.succulentsandsunshine.com_-500x500.jpg\" alt=\"Succulent Terrarium Tutorial Step 1 www.succulentsandsunshine.com\" width=\"500\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Succulent-Terrarium-Tutorial-Step-1-www.succulentsandsunshine.com_-100x100.jpg 100w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Succulent-Terrarium-Tutorial-Step-1-www.succulentsandsunshine.com_-500x500.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Succulent-Terrarium-Tutorial-Step-1-www.succulentsandsunshine.com_-700x700.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Succulent-Terrarium-Tutorial-Step-1-www.succulentsandsunshine.com_.jpg 1000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Once the soil was in I added <a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=terrarium_pearls&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Flisting%2F196882876%2Fsucculent-plant-senecio-rowleyanus%3Fref%3Dshop_home_active_3%26ga_search_query%3Dpearls\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">String of Pearls<\/a> and had them hang out of the main opening.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-4073\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Succulent-Terrarium-Tutorial-Step-2-www.succulentsandsunshine.com_-500x500.jpg\" alt=\"Succulent Terrarium Tutorial Step 2 www.succulentsandsunshine.com\" width=\"500\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Succulent-Terrarium-Tutorial-Step-2-www.succulentsandsunshine.com_-100x100.jpg 100w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Succulent-Terrarium-Tutorial-Step-2-www.succulentsandsunshine.com_-500x500.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Succulent-Terrarium-Tutorial-Step-2-www.succulentsandsunshine.com_-700x700.jpg 700w, https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Succulent-Terrarium-Tutorial-Step-2-www.succulentsandsunshine.com_.jpg 1000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Next I added my two main <a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=terrarium_cuttings&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Flisting%2F224959345%2F25-rosette-succulent-cuttings-1-3inches%3Fref%3Dfavs_view_24\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">succulent cuttings<\/a>\u00a0(I used <a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=terrarium_fred&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Flisting%2F183522790%2Flarge-graptoveria-fred-ives%3Fref%3Dsr_gallery_1%26ga_search_query%3Dfred%2Bives%26ga_search_type%3Dall%26ga_view_type%3Dgallery\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Graptoveria &#8216;Fred Ives'<\/a> and <a href=\"https:\/\/www.awin1.com\/cread.php?awinaffid=233213&awinmid=6220&clickref=terrarium_adolphii&p=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.etsy.com%2Flisting%2F221941623%2Fsucculent-plant-sedum-golden-glow-its%3Fref%3Dshop_home_active_7%26ga_search_query%3Dsedum\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">Sedum Adolphii<\/a>), being sure to put the stems under the soil.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-4074 alignleft\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Succulent-Terrarium-Tutorial-Step-3-www.succulentsandsunshine.com_-225x225.jpg\" alt=\"Succulent Terrarium Tutorial Step 3 www.succulentsandsunshine.com\" width=\"225\" height=\"225\" \/><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-4075\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Succulent-Terrarium-Tutorial-Step-4-www.succulentsandsunshine.com_-225x225.jpg\" alt=\"Succulent Terrarium Tutorial Step 4 www.succulentsandsunshine.com\" width=\"225\" height=\"225\" \/><\/p>\n<p>I used a little bit of <a href=\"https:\/\/www.amazon.com\/gp\/product\/B0081R36OQ\/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=390957&creativeASIN=B0081R36OQ&linkCode=as2&tag=cassituttlpho-20&linkId=AG3JQOZY2L3HC7ML\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow sponsored\">bakers twine<\/a> to hang the terrarium up on my wall. I really like how it turned out! Originally I had planned to put more plants in there, but after playing around with it I realized that simpler was better.<\/p>\n<p>If you try to fit too much in you\u2019ll end up crowding everything and it won\u2019t look very good.<\/p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-6255\" src=\"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2013\/05\/Make-your-own-succulent-terrarium-Its-fun-and-easy-585x877.jpg\" alt=\"Make your own succulent terrarium! It's fun and easy!\" width=\"585\" height=\"877\" \/><\/p>\n<p>I sprayed inside the terrarium with a spray bottle to get all the soil wet. With succulent terrariums you have to make sure you don\u2019t over water. The glass keeps everything trapped in and acts like a mini greenhouse so it will take longer for all the water to evaporate.<\/p>\n<p>I like the design of <a href=\"https:\/\/www.amazon.com\/gp\/product\/B00BUMNEBO?tag=succandsunblog-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener sponsored\">this one<\/a> because it has quite a bit of open space so I don\u2019t think it will get too mushy or cloudy inside which is good. They also have a couple other shapes that you may like as well.<\/p>\n<p>So, don't delay! Get started on your own terrarium!<\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-clearfix\"><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-fullwidth fullwidth-box fusion-builder-row-2 nonhundred-percent-fullwidth non-hundred-percent-height-scrolling\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0);background-position: center center;background-repeat: no-repeat;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;margin-bottom: 0px;margin-top: 0px;border-width: 0px 0px 0px 0px;border-color:#eae9e9;border-style:solid;\" ><div class=\"fusion-builder-row fusion-row\"><div class=\"fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion-builder-column-1 fusion_builder_column_1_1 1_1 fusion-one-full fusion-column-first fusion-column-last\" style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;\"><div class=\"fusion-column-wrapper fusion-flex-column-wrapper-legacy\" style=\"background-position:left top;background-repeat:no-repeat;-webkit-background-size:cover;-moz-background-size:cover;-o-background-size:cover;background-size:cover;padding: 0px 0px 0px 0px;\"><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-2\"><p><span style=\"color: #ffffff;\">.<\/span><\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-clearfix\"><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"","protected":false},"author":7,"featured_media":41597,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[69,31,1],"tags":[81],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/4064"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/7"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=4064"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/4064\/revisions"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/41597"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=4064"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=4064"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.succulentsandsunshine.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=4064"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}